		"description": "<p>Starting at 6th level, you know how to strike in order to disrupt concentration at the expense of your other adept techniques.</p>\n<p>Once per turn, when a creature you can see within 60 feet of you casts a spell, you can spend an exertion point to make a Wisdom (Perception) or Wisdom (Insight) against their spell save DC. On a success, you gain the following effects when you take the Attack action against this creature:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You gain an expertise dice for those attack rolls.</li>\n<li>On a hit, the target&rsquo;s DC for the concentration checks uses your Combat Maneuver DC, or half the damage received, whichever is higher.</li>\n<li>On a hit, the target has disadvantage on checks made to maintain concentration, but has advantage on checks made to resist effects from your Focus Features (such as @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.5wrw48ctsb9sm48o]{Stunning Strike}).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These effects last either for one minute, until you choose to end it, or until you use this feature on a different target.</p>",
